    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6538" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νόος</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">mind,
            understanding, thought;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οὐ γάρ τις νόον ἄλλον ἀμείνονα τοῦδε
            νοήσει</span>, | <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οἷον ἐγὼ νοέω</span>, a
          better ‘view’ than mine,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 9.104</span></i>.
          The word is somewhat flexible in its application, but needs no special
          illustration. Cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νοέω</span>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
